Seventeen years ago, as one of the epidemic areas of Guangdong, I was in the second epidemic area of Beijing University. At that time, I was in the same department under the elder brother's appeal, wrote a month of SARS diary.

My husband and my five-year-old son live in the south of the United States. My husband and his family are from Wuhan. I always go to Wuhan when I go back to China. Last summer, my little friend stayed in Wuhan for more than a month. Luckily, my grandparents came to visit us in late November and stayed with us. On January 21, I went through my SARS diary and came home to see my husband and his cousin on the phone —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— --. Having just relived the memory of SARS, I worried about the possibility of a repeat of the Beijing Blockade. My husband persuaded my cousin to return to Shanghai.

On the morning of the 22nd, my cousin and his family drove back to Shanghai. My uncle and aunt thought it was a big deal and refused to go with them. On the 23rd, Wuhan was "sealed off" .

"teacher, don't go to Wuhan,
Don't go to China, don't go to Japan."

Wednesday, Jan. 22,2020, the weather was clear, the sun was shining and the air was crisp.

I stopped in the motorcade, saw in the rearview mirror that the teacher was leading Xiao out of the waiting area outside the classroom, and pressed the button for the back door to start. However, a turn around, small is not with the teacher. Omasa's teacher put her curly head through the back door, "Xiaozheng seems very, very worried about the Chinese virus, " he told me in a low voice. "He's been talking about it all day, and he seems to know a lot of details and is thinking about it all the time. "

"Oh, maybe we've been talking about it at home! " I recalled.

Indeed, in recent days, especially after academician Zhong Nanshan said on January 20 that 14 medical workers had been infected and confirmed the risk of human to human transmission of the virus, there has been an outbreak of pneumonia in Wuhan, become the sole topic of conversation at our dinner table -- as grandparents feed back information from their circle of friends, sometimes sending a wechat message on the spot to greet a friend; I share information from my circle of friends and Chinese American forums and news articles in English, as well as the various management measures experienced during SARS; my husband May criticize the scientific nature of my grandparents'information, or remind them to talk to a friend who is traveling to visit family, or talk to me about the virus and rethinking the system. Xiaozheng sometimes interrupts to ask us to explain some nouns he doesn't understand.

After Xiaozheng got on the bus, I asked him if he said a lot about the pneumonia virus at school today. "Yes, " Omasa said. "I said to Betsy, 'don't go to Wuhan, don't go to China, don't go to Japan. ' "

"Why? "
"because I was worried that if she went to China, she would be infected. "
"Why can't we go to Japan? "
"because there is one in Japan, " Omasa replied earnestly. "I'm afraid she doesn't know, so I'm going to tell her. "

"It's good that you care about the teacher and tell her these things. But you don't have to worry so much. A lot of our scientists and medical staff are working really hard, and you see now that reagents have been developed very quickly to identify the virus,"I tried to explain in terms he could understand, "It's like the flu. It's a virus. We scientists put a lot of effort into studying it and finding a way around it. Did you get a flu shot last year? With the vaccine, we are not afraid of the flu virus. Now, there are a lot of flu viruses, but we don't have to be afraid. The Wuhan Virus is the same, we have to believe that scientists will soon find a way."

"I'm still worried, " Omasa muttered to himself. "I'm just a worrier. "

I'm worried, too.

I'm worried because Omasa's Chinese school is about to hold a Spring Festival gala, and who knows if there will be new carriers from Wuhan sitting among the parents of the students in the small auditorium.

On Jan. 21, the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention announced the first confirmed case of a new type of coronary pneumonia in Washington state. The patient returned to the United States after traveling to Wuhan. At the same time, the center raised China's tourism Alert Level to Level 2(Practice Enhanced Precautions) : a reminder to Harvard to step up preventive measures.

We may soon have a confirmed case in our own Southeastern United States.

Foreign students are "tumor" students?

On January 24th, I broke new ground on a Chinese wechat group -- a group of people I didn't even know -- in which I read messages and never participated in discussions.

On the same day, however, after Illinois confirmed the second case of new type of coronary pneumonia in the United States (the patient also returned from Wuhan in mid-january) , someone forwarded the news on Wechat Group, "The second case has been confirmed in Chicago of the United States, which is also from Wuhan, so it must be a foreign student from the University of Chicago, " he wrote in Chinese. He was quickly followed by a comment below: "the foreign students are indeed tumor students, carrying the virus... most of the foreign students returned around January 15, when the epidemic had already broken out and was only covered up... "

I couldn't resist responding to the first person: "In her 60s, as you said in your own news link, none of the two confirmed cases in the United States were international students.

A few days ago, my Chinese neighbor's Grandpa Zhang told my grandparents that he was weak and sore and had been lying at home for several days. After a while he asked, your daughter-in-law did not come from Wuhan when she returned to China (I returned to the United States from Guangdong via Hong Kong on January 14) ? As if he knew that our grandparents were from Wuhan and lived in Wuhan, we went to Wuhan almost every time we came back.

In December, Hong Kong was so alarmed by the new virus in Wuhan that the media dubbed it "Wuhan Pneumonia. " My colleagues and I were concerned that such labels were so bad that they only increased mutual distrust, it's not gonNA help with the containment. Soon, the tag was deactivated, but the controls were not relaxed. In mid-january, I arrived in western Guryong Station on a high-speed train, with announcements explaining the new virus in Wuhan and the need for passengers from Wuhan to be examined separately, in addition to infrared temperature readings.

In late January, as the information came to light, my husband looked at pictures of online gatherings of people in Wuhan who were taking the epidemic lightly, angrily accusing them: This is how Wuhan people are. I grew up seeing big, and I haven't changed a bit. I Take Stupidity for granted. I have always argued passionately for the Wuhan Man, as if he were a native Wuhan, even though I was from Guangdong. Such labeling is unfair, even dangerous, and only leads us to ignore the real reason and blame it all on the "backwardness" of a small number of people -- as if they weren't "behind, " they just don't know it yet.

Seventeen years ago, in the school of SARS, I wrote such a diary.

22 May 2003

Today, the Shunfeng Hotel, which passed through the West Gate of the National People's Congress, was reopened, but there was a sign at the door that read: Infectious Diseases are not allowed inside.
Suddenly I wondered if SARS would lead to another form of discrimination, as if there was already one: as if Beijing had become a bit depressed from outside, and I, when SARS came, had to face the constant online criticism of Cantonese, they said that SARS was brought about by their indiscriminate eating, although there was no definitive proof that it was indeed brought about by eating wild game. Unfortunately, there was no significant reduction in the number of people eating wild game in Guangdong, and this time the Wuhan people were accused of the same. For 17 years, there was no system to limit people's eating of wild food. Do people want to rely on self-change of regional food culture to limit it
But what is the use of such censure when we have before us a whole catastrophe? But at that time, I was really embarrassed to say such words, because I am from Guangdong, others sound a little partial flavor. But foreign attitudes toward China now [ in his diary, three days before that time, I noted: "In the evening, Mi showed me an online picture of the cover of time with lung shadows on one Flag of the People's Republic of China. Next: SARS NATION" ] And the original attitude of the outside world to Guangdong, not much different. In their view, the Chinese people do not like clean backward, so here will be the source of SARS, and then (domestic) view of Guangdong, the mentality is no big difference.

New Year's Eve, ready public chopsticks did not use the final

On January 25,2009, just after 7:00 a.m. , there was a thumping sound on the Monitor, and Omasa had recently, for some reason, invented a way to signal that he was awake by tapping the bedplate. I got up and opened his door. I poked my head out and said, "happy New Year. ".

Small is smiling to climb up, to hear this words Leng Leng Leng, remember my yesterday's command, accurately said "mother happy New Year. ". After Washing Gargle, put on his red Tang suit, and grandparents New Year, got his red envelope.

Around 9:20, I calculated the time, and said to my grandfather, let's go to the Chinese supermarket now, in case there will be more people later, it's too early, and I'm afraid that the fresh fish today hasn't arrived yet -- GRANDPA has been preparing for today's feast for nearly a week, Deep Fried Lotus root, fried Balls, stewed beef, stewed spareribs, now only today to buy a fresh fish, good evening on a whole fish.

"Xiao Zheng and grandma are at home, " I said. As she stood up to protest, the grandmother said, let's go, as if we were living in a small community in a rural area of the United States.

"We picked up a suspect at the airport yesterday, " I said. "He took it to the hospital as soon as he got off the plane. He had a fever on the plane, he had been wearing a mask and reported it to the airport. "

Grandma immediately pulled small is sitting down: "We come to tell a story. "

I handed my grandfather a mask, and he took it and turned it over in his hands, covering his face again. "The other way around, " I pointed. "The one with the wire on it. " My grandfather gestured. "I've never worn a mask in my life. "

"It's good to wear a mask in winter, to keep the cold air out of your nose, " I said. "It keeps the virus out. "

GRANDPA tucked his mask into his pocket. "We'll talk about it at the supermarket. "

Around 9:50, we came to the Chinese supermarket, only sparse less than ten people feel, no masks, including sales staff. I took the mask off my face. GRANDPA chose two live fish, picked a spring onion, I took three bags of melon seeds, together to pay the bill. By this time the supermarket was filling up with customers, and I saw two guys wearing masks, N95 masks.

We took the food to the parking lot, GRANDPA suddenly to the front of a family with Wuhan Words said what. The family was supposed to be grandparents, mom, and Darling, and the two, and three year old girl was sitting on a full cart.

I listened carefully, it was probably GRANDPA who greeted them: "You are Wuhan People, too, right? "

That family all smilingly looked back, fellow-townsman's happiness, met fellow-townsman on the day of the Spring Festival in a foreign land, and were fellow-townsman in the epidemic area of home, perhaps that kind of happiness, more than usual some heart to cherish. "Yes, " the grandmother accosted, "you are also a Wuhan, New Year to buy food AH. "

It turned out to be someone I didn't know, I didn't know Wuhan Dialect, I didn't participate in the ability to recognize fellow townsman, then quickly walked forward, ready to open the trunk first, let Grandpa in the back slowly walk and fellow townsman chat.

While chatting, I heard behind the grandfather casually asked: "When did you come? "

"The thirteenth, " replied the grandmother Gaily.

"December 13? " The grandfather obviously hesitated and added a question.

"The 13th of January. "

I didn't look back, but I could feel the air behind me freeze. The second confirmed case in the United States entered the country on January 13. In an eerie silence, GRANDPA caught up with me and got into the car.

Back home, I received a cousin from the WECHAT: "venture to ask a question, you did not go to Wuhan this time? "

My cousin and her family also live in this small town. Although we are not far away from each other, we seldom see each other. But we always have a meal together in the New Year. GRANDPA prepared so many dishes early, at least a little bit to let the cousin family feel the meaning of the Real Wuhan New Year's meal in the inside.

I explained my trip back to the states, talked to her for a few minutes, then put my phone down. By 3:00 pm, I checked my phone and found that my cousin had left me another message, telling us not to go to the Chinese supermarket. I answered. Okay.

After a while, I couldn't help thinking more, and went to find a new set of chopsticks, sAY TO GRANDPA: "How about we use public chopsticks at night? "? I wonder if my cousin would be a little worried, maybe she would feel a little better if she put some chopsticks in the kitchen. " My grandfather, who has been working in the kitchen since lunch, was a little upset: "or don't come, don't come, it doesn't matter, just say early. What's the use of public chopsticks? We're all eating together!"

"maybe it's not that exaggerated, " I was a little embarrassed. "Anyway, if they don't use it, they don't need it, it's fine to use public chopsticks. " I remembered that when I ate in a restaurant in Guangdong, everyone had two pairs of chopsticks in front of them, each in a different color, one for yourself, one for the side dishes. After SARS? After the bird flu? I do not know which node to start, perhaps is such a one epidemic, let everyone slowly changed habits. When I was in Beijing for SARS, I read Albert Camus's book the plague, which said that after the plague, people get memories and knowledge.

It was getting dark, and my cousin's family had not yet appeared. GRANDPA and grandma in the kitchen to and fro to go, dishes are ready, but to wait for people to come before the next pot, or not to eat cold food. Walking up and down, can not help but muttering two "to or not to come. ". For a while, I felt that I really talked too much in the afternoon. I shouldn't talk about the matter of public chopsticks. Maybe it was nothing, but I made them sad.

Everyone in the house was unconcerned and relaxed, but the air seemed to be thin for several minutes, making it difficult to breathe. I stepped out to look at the mailbox, looked outside for a while, and saw a small car coming my way around the corner. I was overjoyed and hurried through the door, shouting, "here they come. "

The kitchen immediately remembered the sound of pots and pans, small is shouting rushed over to call my brother called uncle, grandma also smiled to meet out. Like an oxygen bottle spewing out a large amount of gas, filling the whole room, breathing suddenly relaxed. The Spring Festival came in the midst of a chaotic exchange of "Happy New Year. ".

GRANDPA and grandma a plate of dishes on the table, small positive number and counting, straight a lot of food. None of the cousins noticed the communal chopsticks sitting on the plate, picking up the food directly from the plate with their own chopsticks and stuffing it into their mouths. Their praise for GRANDPA's authentic Wuhan cuisine was incomplete.

After dinner, I tidy up the table, they get together to call home relatives wechat video New Year. Apart from the family of my cousin, who returned to Shanghai the day before the city closure in Wuhan and was immediately isolated at home, the relatives scattered all over Hubei, including those in Wuhan, were all happy to say that life was going on as usual, and their homes would have been full of vegetables for the New Year, i don't even go out anymore. I didn't understand much of the Wuhan dialect, except that they kept repeating to each other, "Yo, are you getting fat? ".

Grandma went to the kitchen to see how I was tidying up. I put a bunch of unused chopsticks in a ziploc bag and sealed it up

"Good, " grandma smilingly, "did not use. "

29 April 2003

... Dinner in Yannan to watch the news, what department issued a false instruction about the May Day in colleges and so on, said to have a meaningful prevention and control of SARS May Day. I have sprayed rice, a look up, the students around are almost the same expression. Smiling all the way home.

On January 27th, the front page of the CDC's COVID-19 website included a map of the United States, the state in which the confirmed case had been found, and a map of the world, the country in which the confirmed case had been found.

Pictures and videos of Prime Minister Li Keqiang's visit to Wuhan were reposted on Wechat. Dr Syzygium aromaticum's report on the epidemic showed that the nationwide confirmed case was 2844 at 8:59 pm on January 27. And the news of Basketball Star Kobe Bryant's plane crash death, in the circle of friends screen.

There's a shortage of masks in Boston

On January 28, I was driving and I heard the news on the radio that there was a shortage of masks in the Boston area as people rushed to pharmacies to buy masks to protect themselves, fearing the spread of new pneumonia. The shortage of masks in Boston is only one of the reasons that local people buy them. It is estimated that more of them are bought by Chinese organizations to support the medical staff in Wuhan.

On the morning of January 30, I got up and saw two pieces of news. One was that the Wuhan Union Hospital was in a hurry, saying that the supplies were not in short supply, but had been exhausted; the other was that the Wuhan Red Cross Society was doing various kinds of inaction, divine operation and justification, and the withholding of donations from the Wuhan Charity General Association.

Seventeen years ago in SARS, I also recorded a donation:

3 May 2003

Time flies, things seem to have not done, papers are still two can not start writing, English almost did not touch. Even though the book is still being read. After doing the differential assignment, I basically threw the economics out the window.

Beijing's Atypical pneumonia is still adding more than a hundred new ones a day, but it seems to have lost its edge. It's a little hokey to warm up at night to collect donations for the medical staff. In those days, when the flood control was low-key, donations were made to the PLA. People don't give much, like $3 or $5.

26 May 2003

The diary of the last day, surprisingly coincidental, in the morning Niu Jun teacher said that from today back to normal classes... in the afternoon, Sparkman class, we have to talk about SARS, have a thesis. So he found his diary, remember a lot about SARS, but can not find a theme to. Warm mentioned a few things in SARS, especially about my attitude to donate money, it is a euphemism criticism.

I forget whether I had ever defended my criticism of Nuan at the time, and perhaps, having grown up hearing too many parents complain about such official donations, I have always been extremely cautious. At that time, we didn't give money because we felt that the medical staff were not good, but we felt that we should not give money through private donations. This was their work, and they should be rewarded for their work, not charity donations. Private donations should not be channelled through such official channels.

The Wenchuan County earthquake of'08. I was in Singapore. I was living on a scholarship. But I couldn't find a way to avoid the authorities, and I ended up donating to the Singapore Red Cross. I still remember standing in front of the ATM and feeling sorry for myself that as a Chinese I had to put my money in the hands of an organization in another country. But I did. I gave away a quarter of my scholarship that month.

On the afternoon of the 30th, I went to our Chinese school counterpart Wuhan Tongji Hospital to fill in some forms of medical supplies. Although it took a lot of effort and personal connections, eventually I had to fill in the recipient's name as Hubei Cishan Association. I compared a lot of organizations before giving money, and finally made sure that there was a direct internal personal connection with the Chinese school, rather than a big pipeline. I mean, the recipient still gets the name, but I'm willing to pay a little bit of money, a little bit of time.

Seventeen years on, my heart is still pessimistic, but my behavior is more optimistic. My maturity came in the form of a greater compromise, a greater effort to believe in the light on the other side. I still have to believe in what I can do, even if it never happens.

On that day, more than 8,000 people were confirmed in China, cases were reported in Tibet, and the country fell. My hometown, Chaozhou, is still struggling, reported in the People's Daily. The group of home-stay operators, who are said to have lost more than 300,000 yuan, a part-time home-stay operator who works for the Transport Bureau and is one of its public employees, posted photos of him working overtime at a highway intersection to check on passing vehicles on a social network.

The World Health Organization (WHO) finally made the announcement, declaring the new pneumonia a "public health emergency of international concern" (PHEIC) . The Donald Trump administration is meeting to discuss. The husband of the second patient, the sixth confirmed case in the United States, confirms the risk of human-to-human Transmission.

The science guy's talking to the nerds

On the night of January 30th America's State Department issued a level four travel warning -- don't go to China. The fourth level is the highest level of travel warnings the State Department can issue, and the same level was issued on January 11th for Iraq, following the attack on a US base there.

Image courtesy of the web

Our Chinese school and the New York Chinese Doctors Association cooperation of the donation, yesterday finally failed to catch the original plane, temporary change of another consignment. In the high-pressure work to do cumbersome form work, the Group of people are strained nerves, a little communication is not smooth on the tone up, we are afraid of late one step channel was blocked. It was originally intended to buy masks, protective clothing, gloves, goggles, masks were canceled, protective clothing and gloves have not yet found the source of supply, in anxiety, the organizers finally decided what to send first, so this time sent out a batch of goggles, some are purchased directly from the manufacturer, others from retail agents, and the shipping cost is about $20,000.

Yesterday, I saw a series of material reports, there are voluntary isolation of the freight drivers, the efforts of girls in the Rice Circle, the hospital procurement staff to seize goods, and the inability of the Red Cross to defend. I don't know if our goggles, after entering Wuhan, can reach the hands of the organizer's old classmate —— Doctor of Wuhan Tongji Hospital. Do what you can. Believe in hope.

Last night I took the outbreak psychological test provided by Ky, overall good, however, in the Depression score, advised me to see less negative news.

I remember a little thing from January 27th, from my husband.

My husband is a typical science student, Prim and logical. On the evening of January 27, he came home from work, sat down at the dinner table, and shared what he and his colleagues had been chatting about over lunch. Here's what he shared:

"everyone is really talking about Wuhan today. Some people say, you Chinese always like to eat strange things, so that this disease. I mean, I've never eaten anything weird myself, and the weirdest thing I've ever eaten is a snake. And they said, "snakes are weird enough. ".

I said, but it seems to me that the French are strange to eat snails, and I think snails are stranger than snakes. They added that it was your Chinese government's mismanagement that caused the disease to spread so badly. I said, this disease is not the same as the flu, the flu is also spread quickly, but this disease has not yet been studied. And they said, "how is this the same as the flu? ". I mean, haven't you heard of the Spanish flu?

And someone actually said No.

I said, the same flu that first appeared in the United States in 1918, swept the world, killed 100 million people, and brought the first world war to an early end. Then they all stopped talking."

He added, "I knew they were going to use this pneumonia thing today. I did my homework early. I looked it up on the Internet and figured out how to say it in English. "

I was happy for his counterattack as a Chinese, and worried for his counterattack as a wife: "So, they have to think, with you as a Chinese, can not have a good conversation. "

On the evening of the day Mr. Schaefer and I shared the story, the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention put all of China on level 3, the highest level of travel warning it can give: avoid unnecessary travel.

Three days later, the US State Department issued its highest level of travel warning -- Level 4, no travel to China.

Four days later, President Donald Trump ordered that no foreigner who had been to China in 14 days should enter the United States.

I'm worried, too.

"Oh, maybe we've been talking about it at home! " I recalled.

Indeed, in recent days, especially after academician Zhong Nanshan said on January 20 that 14 medical workers had been infected and confirmed the risk of human to human transmission of the virus, there has been an outbreak of pneumonia in Wuhan, become the sole topic of conversation at our dinner table -- as grandparents feed back information from their circle of friends, sometimes sending a wechat message on the spot to greet a friend; I share information from my circle of friends and Chinese American forums and news articles in English, as well as the various management measures experienced during SARS; my husband May criticize the scientific nature of my grandparents'information, or remind them to talk to a friend who is traveling to visit family, or talk to me about the virus and rethinking the system. Xiaozheng sometimes interrupts to ask us to explain some nouns he doesn't understand.

After Xiaozheng got on the bus, I asked him if he said a lot about the pneumonia virus at school today. "Yes, " Omasa said. "I said to Betsy, 'don't go to Wuhan, don't go to China, don't go to Japan. ' "

"Why? "

"because I was worried that if she went to China, she would be infected. "

"Why can't we go to Japan? "

"because there is one in Japan, " Omasa replied earnestly. "I'm afraid she doesn't know, so I'm going to tell her. "

"It's good that you care about the teacher and tell her these things. But you don't have to worry so much. A lot of our scientists and medical staff are working really hard, and you see now that reagents have been developed very quickly to identify the virus,"I tried to explain in terms he could understand, "It's like the flu. It's a virus. We scientists put a lot of effort into studying it and finding a way around it. Did you get a flu shot last year? With the vaccine, we are not afraid of the flu virus. Now, there are a lot of flu viruses, but we don't have to be afraid. The Wuhan Virus is the same, we have to believe that scientists will soon find a way."

"I'm still worried, " Omasa muttered to himself. "I'm just a worrier. "

Foreign students are "tumor" students?

On January 24th, I broke new ground on a Chinese wechat group -- a group of people I didn't even know -- in which I read messages and never participated in discussions.

On the same day, however, after Illinois confirmed the second case of new type of coronary pneumonia in the United States (the patient also returned from Wuhan in mid-january) , someone forwarded the news on Wechat Group, "The second case has been confirmed in Chicago of the United States, which is also from Wuhan, so it must be a foreign student from the University of Chicago, " he wrote in Chinese. He was quickly followed by a comment below: "the foreign students are indeed tumor students, carrying the virus... most of the foreign students returned around January 15, when the epidemic had already broken out and was only covered up... "

I couldn't resist responding to the first person: "In her 60s, as you said in your own news link, none of the two confirmed cases in the United States were international students.

A few days ago, my Chinese neighbor's Grandpa Zhang told my grandparents that he was weak and sore and had been lying at home for several days. After a while he asked, your daughter-in-law did not come from Wuhan when she returned to China (I returned to the United States from Guangdong via Hong Kong on January 14) ? As if he knew that our grandparents were from Wuhan and lived in Wuhan, we went to Wuhan almost every time we came back.

In December, Hong Kong was so alarmed by the new virus in Wuhan that the media dubbed it "Wuhan Pneumonia. " My colleagues and I were concerned that such labels were so bad that they only increased mutual distrust, it's not gonNA help with the containment. Soon, the tag was deactivated, but the controls were not relaxed. In mid-january, I arrived in western Guryong Station on a high-speed train, with announcements explaining the new virus in Wuhan and the need for passengers from Wuhan to be examined separately, in addition to infrared temperature readings.

In late January, as the information came to light, my husband looked at pictures of online gatherings of people in Wuhan who were taking the epidemic lightly, angrily accusing them: This is how Wuhan people are. I grew up seeing big, and I haven't changed a bit. I Take Stupidity for granted. I have always argued passionately for the Wuhan Man, as if he were a native Wuhan, even though I was from Guangdong. Such labeling is unfair, even dangerous, and only leads us to ignore the real reason and blame it all on the "backwardness" of a small number of people -- as if they weren't "behind, " they just don't know it yet.

Around 9:20, I calculated the time, and said to my grandfather, let's go to the Chinese supermarket now, in case there will be more people later, it's too early, and I'm afraid that the fresh fish today hasn't arrived yet -- GRANDPA has been preparing for today's feast for nearly a week, Deep Fried Lotus root, fried Balls, stewed beef, stewed spareribs, now only today to buy a fresh fish, good evening on a whole fish.

"We picked up a suspect at the airport yesterday, " I said. "He took it to the hospital as soon as he got off the plane. He had a fever on the plane, he had been wearing a mask and reported it to the airport. "

Grandma immediately pulled small is sitting down: "We come to tell a story. "

I handed my grandfather a mask, and he took it and turned it over in his hands, covering his face again. "The other way around, " I pointed. "The one with the wire on it. " My grandfather gestured. "I've never worn a mask in my life. "

"It's good to wear a mask in winter, to keep the cold air out of your nose, " I said. "It keeps the virus out. "

GRANDPA tucked his mask into his pocket. "We'll talk about it at the supermarket. "

Around 9:50, we came to the Chinese supermarket, only sparse less than ten people feel, no masks, including sales staff. I took the mask off my face. GRANDPA chose two live fish, picked a spring onion, I took three bags of melon seeds, together to pay the bill. By this time the supermarket was filling up with customers, and I saw two guys wearing masks, N95 masks.

We took the food to the parking lot, GRANDPA suddenly to the front of a family with Wuhan Words said what. The family was supposed to be grandparents, mom, and Darling, and the two, and three year old girl was sitting on a full cart.

I listened carefully, it was probably GRANDPA who greeted them: "You are Wuhan People, too, right? "

That family all smilingly looked back, fellow-townsman's happiness, met fellow-townsman on the day of the Spring Festival in a foreign land, and were fellow-townsman in the epidemic area of home, perhaps that kind of happiness, more than usual some heart to cherish. "Yes, " the grandmother accosted, "you are also a Wuhan, New Year to buy food AH. "

It turned out to be someone I didn't know, I didn't know Wuhan Dialect, I didn't participate in the ability to recognize fellow townsman, then quickly walked forward, ready to open the trunk first, let Grandpa in the back slowly walk and fellow townsman chat.

While chatting, I heard behind the grandfather casually asked: "When did you come? "

"The thirteenth, " replied the grandmother Gaily.

"December 13? " The grandfather obviously hesitated and added a question.

"The 13th of January. "

I didn't look back, but I could feel the air behind me freeze. The second confirmed case in the United States entered the country on January 13. In an eerie silence, GRANDPA caught up with me and got into the car.

Back home, I received a cousin from the WECHAT: "venture to ask a question, you did not go to Wuhan this time? "

My cousin and her family also live in this small town. Although we are not far away from each other, we seldom see each other. But we always have a meal together in the New Year. GRANDPA prepared so many dishes early, at least a little bit to let the cousin family feel the meaning of the Real Wuhan New Year's meal in the inside.

I explained my trip back to the states, talked to her for a few minutes, then put my phone down. By 3:00 pm, I checked my phone and found that my cousin had left me another message, telling us not to go to the Chinese supermarket. I answered. Okay.

After a while, I couldn't help thinking more, and went to find a new set of chopsticks, sAY TO GRANDPA: "How about we use public chopsticks at night? "? I wonder if my cousin would be a little worried, maybe she would feel a little better if she put some chopsticks in the kitchen. " My grandfather, who has been working in the kitchen since lunch, was a little upset: "or don't come, don't come, it doesn't matter, just say early. What's the use of public chopsticks? We're all eating together!"

"maybe it's not that exaggerated, " I was a little embarrassed. "Anyway, if they don't use it, they don't need it, it's fine to use public chopsticks. " I remembered that when I ate in a restaurant in Guangdong, everyone had two pairs of chopsticks in front of them, each in a different color, one for yourself, one for the side dishes. After SARS? After the bird flu? I do not know which node to start, perhaps is such a one epidemic, let everyone slowly changed habits. When I was in Beijing for SARS, I read Albert Camus's book the plague, which said that after the plague, people get memories and knowledge.

It was getting dark, and my cousin's family had not yet appeared. GRANDPA and grandma in the kitchen to and fro to go, dishes are ready, but to wait for people to come before the next pot, or not to eat cold food. Walking up and down, can not help but muttering two "to or not to come. ". For a while, I felt that I really talked too much in the afternoon. I shouldn't talk about the matter of public chopsticks. Their praise for GRANDPA's authentic Wuhan cuisine was incomplete.

There's a shortage of masks in Boston

On January 28, I was driving and I heard the news on the radio that there was a shortage of masks in the Boston area as people rushed to pharmacies to buy masks to protect themselves, fearing the spread of new pneumonia. The shortage of masks in Boston is only one of the reasons that local people buy them. It is estimated that more of them are bought by Chinese organizations to support the medical staff in Wuhan.

On the morning of January 30, I got up and saw two pieces of news. One was that the Wuhan Union Hospital was in a hurry, saying that the supplies were not in short supply, but had been exhausted; the other was that the Wuhan Red Cross Society was doing various kinds of inaction, divine operation and justification, and the withholding of donations from the Wuhan Charity General Association.

So he found his diary, remember a lot about SARS, but can not find a theme to. Warm mentioned a few things in SARS, especially about my attitude to donate money, it is a euphemism criticism.

I forget whether I had ever defended my criticism of Nuan at the time, and perhaps, having grown up hearing too many parents complain about such official donations, I have always been extremely cautious. At that time, we didn't give money because we felt that the medical staff were not good, but we felt that we should not give money through private donations. This was their work, and they should be rewarded for their work, not charity donations. Private donations should not be channelled through such official channels.

The Wenchuan County earthquake of'08. I was in Singapore. I was living on a scholarship. But I couldn't find a way to avoid the authorities, and I ended up donating to the Singapore Red Cross. I still remember standing in front of the ATM and feeling sorry for myself that as a Chinese I had to put my money in the hands of an organization in another country. But I did. I gave away a quarter of my scholarship that month.

On the afternoon of the 30th, I went to our Chinese school counterpart Wuhan Tongji Hospital to fill in some forms of medical supplies. Although it took a lot of effort and personal connections, eventually I had to fill in the recipient's name as Hubei Cishan Association. I compared a lot of organizations before giving money, and finally made sure that there was a direct internal personal connection with the Chinese school, rather than a big pipeline. I mean, the recipient still gets the name, but I'm willing to pay a little bit of money, a little bit of time.

Seventeen years on, my heart is still pessimistic, but my behavior is more optimistic. My maturity came in the form of a greater compromise, a greater effort to believe in the light on the other side. I still have to believe in what I can do, even if it never happens.

On that day, more than 8,000 people were confirmed in China, cases were reported in Tibet, and the country fell. My hometown, Chaozhou, is still struggling, reported in the People's Daily. The group of home-stay operators, who are said to have lost more than 300,000 yuan, a part-time home-stay operator who works for the Transport Bureau and is one of its public employees, posted photos of him working overtime at a highway intersection to check on passing vehicles on a social network.

The World Health Organization (WHO) finally made the announcement, declaring the new pneumonia a "public health emergency of international concern" (PHEIC) . The Donald Trump administration is meeting to discuss. The husband of the second patient, the sixth confirmed case in the United States, confirms the risk of human-to-human Transmission.

The science guy's talking to the nerds

On the night of January 30th America's State Department issued a level four travel warning -- don't go to China. The fourth level is the highest level of travel warnings the State Department can issue, and the same level was issued on January 11th for Iraq, following the attack on a US base there.

Our Chinese school and the New York Chinese Doctors Association cooperation of the donation, yesterday finally failed to catch the original plane, temporary change of another consignment. In the high-pressure work to do cumbersome form work, the Group of people are strained nerves, a little communication is not smooth on the tone up, we are afraid of late one step channel was blocked. It was originally intended to buy masks, protective clothing, gloves, goggles, masks were canceled, protective clothing and gloves have not yet found the source of supply, in anxiety, the organizers finally decided what to send first, so this time sent out a batch of goggles, some are purchased directly from the manufacturer, others from retail agents, and the shipping cost is about $20,000.

Yesterday, I saw a series of material reports, there are voluntary isolation of the freight drivers, the efforts of girls in the Rice Circle, the hospital procurement staff to seize goods, and the inability of the Red Cross to defend. I don't know if our goggles, after entering Wuhan, can reach the hands of the organizer's old classmate —— Doctor of Wuhan Tongji Hospital. Do what you can. Believe in hope.

Last night I took the outbreak psychological test provided by Ky, overall good, however, in the Depression score, advised me to see less negative news.

I remember a little thing from January 27th, from my husband.

My husband is a typical science student, Prim and logical. On the evening of January 27, he came home from work, sat down at the dinner table, and shared what he and his colleagues had been chatting about over lunch. Here's what he shared:

"everyone is really talking about Wuhan today. Some people say, you Chinese always like to eat strange things, so that this disease. I mean, I've never eaten anything weird myself, and the weirdest thing I've ever eaten is a snake. And they said, "snakes are weird enough. ".

I said, but it seems to me that the French are strange to eat snails, and I think snails are stranger than snakes. They added that it was your Chinese government's mismanagement that caused the disease to spread so badly. I said, this disease is not the same as the flu, the flu is also spread quickly, but this disease has not yet been studied. And they said, "how is this the same as the flu? ". I mean, haven't you heard of the Spanish flu?

And someone actually said No.

I said, the same flu that first appeared in the United States in 1918, swept the world, killed 100 million people, and brought the first world war to an early end. Then they all stopped talking."

He added, "I knew they were going to use this pneumonia thing today. I did my homework early. I looked it up on the Internet and figured out how to say it in English. "

I was happy for his counterattack as a Chinese, and worried for his counterattack as a wife: "So, they have to think, with you as a Chinese, can not have a good conversation. "

On the evening of the day Mr. Schaefer and I shared the story, the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention put all of China on level 3, the highest level of travel warning it can give: avoid unnecessary travel.

Three days later, the US State Department issued its highest level of travel warning -- Level 4, no travel to China.
